Reliance Industries Ltd., Indiaâ€™s
largest company by market value, started marketing its sale of
bonds denominated in U.S. dollars, according to a person
familiar with the matter.  Reliance is offering investors 10-year notes to yield about
212 1/2 basis points more than similar-maturity Treasuries and
30-year bonds at about 250 basis points over Treasuries, said
the person, who asked not to be identified because the details
are private.  Reliance Holding USA Inc. is selling the bonds and Reliance
Industries is guaranteeing them.  To contact the reporter on this story:
